The Confederation of African Football (CAF) has given a nod to the request of the Ghana Football Association (GFA) to have a full capacity at the Baba Yara Sports Stadium for the Qatar 2022 World Cup Play-off involving Ghana and Nigeria. In a statement by GFA, the continental football ruling body has approved their request as long as it follows the laid down rules by CAF. In view of this, GFA has urged fans to adhere to the laid down security guidelines for the game.   StarTimes to beam Ghana, Nigeria cracker     Falconets hopes to complete double against Senegal     Confident Iheanacho tips Nigeria to edge Ghana    “CAF has approved Ghana’s request to admit 40,000 spectators for the FIFA World Cup Qatar 202 play-off first leg match against Nigeria at the Baba Yara Stadium in Kumasi.” “This comes after GFA request to play the game in full capacity stadium following laid down rules by CAF.” “The GFA consequently advise all Ghanaians to obey laid-down safety and security measures strictly to first and foremost have a successful match and also to avoid any sanctions from CAF and FIFA.”  “Meanwhile, fans are advised to strictly adhere to the designated spectators and stakeholders’ entry points and gates for verification of their tickets,” stated the GFA statement.